ThemeConfig get_site_theme Method Fix - January 2025

Overview
Fixed critical missing method get_site_theme in Comserv::Model::ThemeConfig that was causing application crashes when themes were being loaded.

Problem
Application was throwing exception:
Can't locate object method "get_site_theme" via package "Comserv::Model::ThemeConfig" at /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2/Comserv/script/../lib/Comserv/Controller/Root.pm line 1120.

Root Cause
The get_site_theme method was missing from the ThemeConfig model but was being called by the Root controller to determine site-specific themes.

Solution
Implemented the missing get_site_theme method with the following features:

Method Functionality
- Site-to-theme mapping: Maps site names to themes using site_themes configuration from theme_definitions.json
- Session caching: Caches theme selections in user session for performance
- Fallback handling: Returns 'default' theme if no mapping found or on errors
- Case normalization: Handles case-insensitive site name matching
- Validation: Verifies selected theme exists in theme definitions
- Comprehensive logging: Logs all theme selection decisions for debugging

Method Signature
sub get_site_theme {
    my ($self, $c, $site_name) = @_;
    return $theme_name;
}

Configuration Integration
Uses the site_themes section from /root/static/config/theme_definitions.json:
{
  "site_themes": {
    "default": "default",
    "apis": "apis", 
    "usbm": "usbm",
    "csc": "csc",
    "bmaster": "apis",
    "mcoop": "mcoop"
  }
}

Files Modified
- /Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/ThemeConfig.pm - Added missing get_site_theme method

Testing
- Application now starts without crashes
- Theme selection works correctly for all configured sites
- Session-based theme caching is functional
- Proper fallback to default theme when no mapping exists

Deployment Impact
- Zero downtime: Method addition is backwards compatible
- No configuration changes needed: Uses existing theme configuration
- Immediate effect: Application restart automatically picks up the fix

Related Issues
This fix resolves the controller-level exception that was preventing proper theme application across the system.